19 1681 et seq.; 34 C.F.R. Part 106) Sections 2-6 of this bill provide, in skeleton form,
20 that, if any of these federal laws or regulations are repealed by the Federal
21 Government, the provisions of the repealed federal laws or regulations, as they
22 existed on July 1, 2025, continue to apply in this State. Section 2 additionally
23 provides that, if the Individuals with Disabilities Education Act is repealed, a
24 person who previously had the right to bring a civil action in a district court of the
25 United States is authorized to bring such an action in a court of competent
26 jurisdiction of this State. Section 7 of this bill makes a conforming change to
27 indicate the proper placement of section 1 in the Nevada Revised Statutes.
